      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "The fresh and somewhat older wind slabs can be released easily by a single winter sport participant in all aspects. Avalanche prone locations are to be found in gullies and bowls, and behind abrupt changes in the terrain above approximately 2000 m. The prevalence of avalanche prone locations and likelihood of triggering will increase with altitude. Avalanches can reach medium size. <br/> Shooting cracks when stepping on the snowpack can indicate the danger. <br/> <br/> Avalanches can in isolated cases be triggered in near-ground layers and reach large size in isolated cases. The avalanche prone locations are to be found in particular on very steep west, north and east facing slopes above approximately 2000 m. <br/> <br/> Backcountry touring calls for experience in the assessment of avalanche danger.",
        "highlights": "Wind slabs and weakly bonded old snow require caution."
      },
